cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of maximum sum rate of slotted Aloha networks with Successive Interference Cancellation (SIC) receivers. This involves the study of information transmission and decoding, which falls under the purview of Information Theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of slotted Aloha networks, which is a fundamental protocol in networking. The study of the impact of SIC on the network performance also falls under the domain of Networking and Internet Architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the analysis of a communication system with SIC receivers, which involves the study of system dynamics and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the analysis of the effect of multipacket reception (MPR) on the sum rate performance, which is relevant in multimedia applications where multiple packets are transmitted simultaneously. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of slotted Aloha networks with SIC receivers, which falls under the domain of Performance evaluation and analysis.
